## 🔍 Overview

Phishing is one of the most prevalent forms of cybercrime, where attackers deceive victims using social engineering or fake websites to steal sensitive information such as passwords, usernames, and financial credentials.

This project uses **machine learning** to detect phishing URLs by analysing 30 handcrafted features extracted from a URL — including domain structure, HTTPS usage, website traffic, and more. A **Gradient Boosting Classifier** was selected as the final model after benchmarking 10 different algorithms, achieving **97.4% accuracy**.

The model is deployed as a **Flask web application** where users can paste any URL and instantly receive a safety prediction.

---

## ⚙️ How It Works

```
User submits URL
      │
      ▼
Feature Extraction (30 features)
      │
      ▼
Gradient Boosting Classifier
      │
      ▼
Prediction: Safe / Phishing (with probability score)
```

1. The user enters a URL in the web interface.
2. The `FeatureExtraction` class analyses the URL and extracts 30 numerical features.
3. The trained GBC model predicts whether the URL is **safe** or **phishing**.
4. A probability score is returned and displayed to the user.

---

## 🧮 Features Extracted

The model uses 30 features grouped into three categories:

### URL-Based Features
| # | Feature | Description |
|---|---------|-------------|
| 1 | Using IP Address | Checks if an IP address is used instead of a domain name |
| 2 | URL Length | Flags unusually long URLs (>75 chars) |
| 3 | URL Shortening | Detects known shorteners like bit.ly, tinyurl |
| 4 | `@` Symbol | Presence of `@` forces browser to ignore preceding text |
| 5 | Redirecting `//` | Double slash beyond position 7 signals redirect |
| 6 | Prefix/Suffix `-` | Hyphen in domain name is a phishing indicator |
| 7 | Sub-Domain Count | Multiple sub-domains increase phishing likelihood |

### Domain-Based Features
| # | Feature | Description |
|---|---------|-------------|
| 8 | HTTPS | Checks if HTTPS is used |
| 9 | Domain Registration Length | Short registration periods are suspicious |
| 10 | Favicon | Favicon loaded from a different domain signals phishing |
| 11 | Non-Standard Port | Use of unusual ports |
| 12 | HTTPS in Domain URL | "https" appearing in the domain part of the URL |

### HTML & JavaScript Features
| # | Feature | Description |
|---|---------|-------------|
| 13 | Request URL | Percentage of external resources loaded |
| 14 | Anchor URL | Percentage of anchor tags pointing externally |
| 15 | Links in `<script>` / `<link>` | Ratio of external script and link tags |
| 16 | Server Form Handler | Form action pointing to blank or external pages |
| 17 | Info Email | Use of `mailto:` in page |
| 18 | Abnormal URL | Host name not matching WHOIS response |
| 19 | Website Forwarding | Excessive redirects |
| 20 | Status Bar Customisation | `onmouseover` used to hide real URL |
| 21 | Disable Right Click | Right-click disabled via JavaScript |
| 22 | Popup Window | Use of `alert()` |
| 23 | Iframe Redirection | Invisible iframes to load malicious content |

### Domain/Traffic-Based Features
| # | Feature | Description |
|---|---------|-------------|
| 24 | Age of Domain | Domains < 6 months old are suspicious |
| 25 | DNS Record | Missing DNS record signals phishing |
| 26 | Website Traffic | Alexa rank below 100,000 indicates legitimacy |
| 27 | Page Rank | Google PageRank score |
| 28 | Google Index | Whether the URL is indexed by Google |
| 29 | Links Pointing to Page | Number of external links pointing to the page |
| 30 | Statistical Reports | URL/IP matching known phishing blacklists |

---

## 📊 Model Performance

Ten machine learning algorithms were trained and evaluated on the dataset:

| Rank | Model | Accuracy | F1 Score | Recall | Precision |
|------|-------|----------|----------|--------|-----------|
| 🥇 1 | **Gradient Boosting Classifier** | **0.974** | **0.977** | **0.994** | **0.986** |
| 🥈 2 | CatBoost Classifier | 0.972 | 0.975 | 0.994 | 0.989 |
| 🥉 3 | XGBoost Classifier | 0.969 | 0.973 | 0.993 | 0.984 |
| 4 | Multi-layer Perceptron | 0.969 | 0.973 | 0.995 | 0.981 |
| 5 | Random Forest | 0.967 | 0.971 | 0.993 | 0.990 |
| 6 | Support Vector Machine | 0.964 | 0.968 | 0.980 | 0.965 |
| 7 | Decision Tree | 0.960 | 0.964 | 0.991 | 0.993 |
| 8 | K-Nearest Neighbors | 0.956 | 0.961 | 0.991 | 0.989 |
| 9 | Logistic Regression | 0.934 | 0.941 | 0.943 | 0.927 |
| 10 | Naive Bayes Classifier | 0.605 | 0.454 | 0.292 | 0.997 |

> **Gradient Boosting Classifier** was selected as the final model with **97.4% accuracy**.

### Feature Importance

The top features influencing the model's decisions:

![Feature Importance](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/79131292/144603941-19044aae-7d7b-4e9a-88a8-6adfd8626f77.png)

Key findings:
- **HTTPS**, **AnchorURL**, and **WebsiteTraffic** are the most important features.
- Domain age and DNS records are also strong indicators.

